               <head>Commentary on Rumi’s Masnavi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Javāhir al-asrār va zavāhir al-anvār by Ḥusayn ibn Ḥasan al-Khvārazmī, fl. early 15th cent.</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_983-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_114789698">Ḥusayn ibn Ḥasan al-Khvārazmī, fl. early 15th cent.</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_114789698">حسين ابن حسن الخوارزمى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1867">Javāhir al-asrār va zavāhir al-anvār</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_1867">جواهر الاسرار و زواهر الانوار</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Commentary by <persName key="person_114789698" role="aut">Ḥusayn ibn Ḥasan al-Khvārazmī</persName> (d. 830/1426 or 840/1436) on the first daftar from the <title>Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title> of the poet, <persName key="person_98930150" role="ant">Jalāl al-Dīn Muḥammad Rūmī Balkhī</persName>. The work appears to have been commissioned by the <persName key="person_f7562" role="pat">Shah of Khvarazm</persName>, <persName key="person_f7562" role="pat">Nāṣir al-Dīn Abū al-Manāqib</persName>, and <persName key="person_f1545" role="pat">Prince Ibrāhīm Sulṭān</persName>, through the mediation of the deceased amīr, <persName key="person_f7132" role="pat">Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn Abū al-Fatḥ Shāh Malik Bahādur</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is prefixed by a detailed muqaddimah or introduction divided into ten maqālah, discussing the nature of light, cosmogony, prophecy, the lives of prominent Ṣūfī saints, doctrines, terminology, and initiation. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective at the beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Folio 100r left blank, marked with the phrase <q>ṣaḥīḥ al-bayāz̤</q>; miscellaneous verses added later. Folio 113r left blank. Preceding folio gives folio count as 113 varq.
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 301v): 4 Rabīʿ al-S̲ānī 1051/13 July 1641. Matter following the colophon includes poems and medicinal recipes (ff. 301v-302v). 
</p>
                        <p>Marbled cover preserved with IOL red leather binding; net overlay on some folios; wormholes and stains. 
</p>
                        <p>Ownership seal and inscriptions (f. 1v): (circular seal) <persName key="person_f7021" role="fmo">ʿAbd Allāh khānah'zād-i ʿĀlamgīr Pādshāh</persName> [RY] 22; 1) from the property of <persName key="person_f7110" role="fmo">Dilīr Himmat</persName>, [regnal] year 28, transferred to <persName key="person_f7341" role="fmo">Muḥammad Bāqir</persName>, 27 Jumādá al-S̲ānī [regnal] year 28; 2) 8 Ramaz̤ān [regnal] year 29, transferred to <persName key="person_f7351" role="fmo">Muḥammad Fāz̤il</persName>. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
